description.propertyDetail: Be sure to consider this well-maintained home w/both the inside & outside features you are looking for. Plenty of parking space available w/a large concrete apron, fenced-in yard, 2-car insulated garage w/electric, & an area for your boat, RV, or the like. Step inside & walk into the kitchen w/new appliances, farm sink, local custom cabinetry, butcher block island & counters together with a bench-style dining area, & convenient laundry area w/extra counter & cabinets. Large living room shared w/dining w/hardwood flooring, built-in shelving, wood stove, & enclosed front porch sitting/relaxing. Main-level bedroom features a recently updated 3/4 bath. You will not want to miss the larger main-level bathroom featuring custom tile shower, double vanity marble top, vessel sinks, waterproof flooring, cove lighting, & an in-ceiling heater. A rebuilt staircase leads you to the second story bedroom that could function as two bedrooms--w/ample closet space & no-scuff vinyl flooring. Much more!

Tucked on the end of a quiet cul de sac, this beautiful home has the feel of country with the convenience of town. Built in 1996 by Connor & Smith, this cedar sided home has been meticulously maintained. Spacious kitchen and living room with fireplace on the main level, along with master suite and renovated master bath. Two additional bedrooms on the second level, with renovated bathroom and additional family room. A walkout basement, with a large workshop area, half bath and finished family room. This property boasts a massive, custom built heated shop, with half bath, private office and three overhead doors. The shop is perfect for storing your equipment, entertaining family and friends or using as additional living space. Updates are numerous; new roof, new drywall throughout, exterior Hardy stove, renovated bathrooms, new flooring throughout, remodeled kitchen, new doors, new decks, wood siding recently stained.

WELL-KEPT PRIVATE LOCATION SOUTHGATE CONDO. 1, 132 sq. ft. Big living room/dining combo, open plan to kitchen. Two bedrooms, one with ensuite shower with built-in seat, toilet, basin, medicine cupboard, large walk-in closet. 2nd full bathroom with washer/ dryer. Single car garage; extra parking for two more cars not obstructing garage. Cute patio looking out towards the communal gazebo. These units have sold quickly especially in the recent market. Covenants apply. HOA fees $127.50 a month.

This Multi-family Apartment building has 4 units. Located just a few blocks from the center of town and very close to grocery stores, restaurants, and schools. This building has an $18, 087 annual net income after expenses. Tenants rent includes utilities of Fairfield Water, Alliant Energy, & Windstream Internet. Tenants need 24 hours notice to show.

Charming 1920's Craftsman adjacent to Chautauqua Park. This home features 3 bedrooms (+ office) and 2 bathrooms. With the living room (featuring a gas fireplace) in the front and large sunny family room in the back, there is ample space for everyone in this lovely home. Hardwood floors and leaded windows add to the charm, and the location can't be beat! Recent updates include interior and exterior paint, new gas fireplace and furnace. Impeccably clean and absolutely move-in ready!

Great location for this 1-story bungalow! With close to 1, 100 square feet and all the living on the main level, this home features a large kitchen with ample cabinets & counter space as well as room for an eat-in feature. Sits adjacent to the dining room with views of the living area. Front living room with great space for furniture. Large foyer area leads to the bedrooms each with closets. Hallway 3/4 bath. Mudroom also functions as the laundry. Great space in the 2-car detached garage & includes large concrete parking apron. Centrally located and within walking distance to downtown, Everybody's, & additional shopping make this property one to consider.

This east facing quality brick home on cul-de-sac near Fairfield Golf & Country Club is move in ready! High ceilings, skylights and new paint freshens the large living room with fireplace and glass door to deck. Adjacent kitchen has vaulted ceilings, dark granite counters, open dining space, built in shelving, desk space, hardwood floors and lots of pantry space. Main floor has private very large ensuite with jetted tub, walk in shower, his-&-hers vanities and big walk in closet. On the other side of the main floor in an additional bedroom with double closets next to a full bath. Tiled floored 4 Seasons room with many windows also has deck access facing private wooded back yard. Main-floor laundry duals as garage entry mud room with cabinets and sink. Lower level features third bedroom with egress window, a third full bath, another potential bedroom or office, finished family room and additional space to finish while still having lots of storage space. Two-car attached garage.
